From 267430e1cd963191bba903942319997927e624a6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Kooran Paul, Princy" <princy.kooran.paul@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 16 May 2024 07:51:40 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 11/46] drm/i915: Bypass gem_set_tiling and gem_get_tiling

gem_set_tiling and gem_get_tiling are deprecated. However this
check is still required for legacy user space process to avoid
getting KMS error.

Add SRIOV check to ensure sriov is not getting error on vf.

Signed-off-by: Chew, Tong Liang <tong.liang.chew@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Zawawi, Muhammad Zul Husni <muhammad.zul.husni.zawawi@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/gem/i915_gem_tiling.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/gem/i915_gem_tiling.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/gem/i915_gem_tiling.c
index 5a296ba3758a..55e9935a67b0 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/gem/i915_gem_tiling.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/gem/i915_gem_tiling.c
@@ -347,7 +347,7 @@ i915_gem_set_tiling_ioctl(struct drm_device *dev, void *data,
 	struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj;
 	int err;
 
-	if (!to_gt(i915)->ggtt->num_fences)
+	if (!to_gt(i915)->ggtt->num_fences && !IS_SRIOV_VF(i915))
 		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 
 	obj = i915_gem_object_lookup(file, args->handle);
@@ -430,7 +430,7 @@ i915_gem_get_tiling_ioctl(struct drm_device *dev, void *data,
 	struct drm_i915_gem_object *obj;
 	int err = -ENOENT;
 
-	if (!to_gt(i915)->ggtt->num_fences)
+	if (!to_gt(i915)->ggtt->num_fences && !IS_SRIOV_VF(i915))
 		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 
 	rcu_read_lock();
-- 
